The imagery of Daniel 7 is the role the beasts play in the last days of Ancient Israel. The context clearly focuses on judgment, the parousia, and the destruction of the enemies of God. In that respect, the chapter is an enlargement and recapitulation of the vision of chapter two. This is one of the ways in which Daniel's book follows the format of visions in the book of Revelation.

