			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The subject of the resurrection and inheriting the kingdom of God focuses on the status of Christians as true covenant sons of God. Resurrection is about sons whose privilege through faith entitles them to the inheritance in the kingdom of God. This is why Christ refers to them as &#8220;sons of the resurrection.&#8221;</p>
<p>On the other hand, those who inherit the kingdom of God, likewise are sons. Inheritance conveys the idea of those in relationship to the Benefactor, i.e. to Christ who inherits the kingdom. As joint-heirs Christians have inherited with him.</p>
<p>We discuss this topic in more detail to assist you in understanding how to interpret 1 Corinthians 15:50 in the light of soteriology and eschatology versus biology and genealogy.  For more assistance, see the full article at <a title="Kingdom of God" href="http://www.allthingsfulfilled.com/eschatology/flesh-and-blood-shall-not-inherit-the-kingdom-of-god" target="_blank">allthingsfulfilled.com</a>
</p>
